  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/application-development-discussions/sap-developer-challenge-apis-task-12-use-the-access-token-to-call-the-api/m-p/283209#M3822</id>
    <title>Re: SAP Developer Challenge - APIs - Task 12 - Use the access token to call the API endpoint</title>
    <updated>2023-08-30T08:06:11.392000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>seVladimirs</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/312</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;I got stuck for a few minutes to refresh my token as I was sending `access_token` and not `refresh_token` 🫣 learned something new!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;As this is a last challenge I would like to say thanks&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/53"&gt;@qmacro&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;for this amazing SAP Developer Challenges! The timing of posting all the challenges was just perfect for me. It was matching with the time when I usually read blog posts and enjoy a quiet morning coffee before kicking off my workday. &lt;span class="lia-unicode-emoji" title=":thumbs_up:"&gt;👍&lt;/span&gt; I've learned a lot, but not yet fully converted to "terminal-only" user &lt;span class="lia-unicode-emoji" title=":upside_down_face:"&gt;🙃&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(I've used `insomnia.rest` as replacement for curl 🤫 )&amp;nbsp;so looking forward for more blog posts, challenges, or perhaps we should plan CodeJam in Riga on this topic 🤩&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/application-development-discussions/sap-developer-challenge-apis-task-12-use-the-access-token-to-call-the-api/m-p/283209#M3822"/>
    <published>2023-08-30T08:06:11.392000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
